channel.title: [HELP] Problem with cannot find symbol
channel.description:
Well I kinda feel like I need help more than I should but oh well... So I've been trying to do Joe9099's shop tutorial at RaGEZONE and I'll give you a link to it so you can look over it... So I've solved every error I've come across so far but I can't fix this error I get when I compile..
Link to Joe's tut -- [URL=http://"http://forum.ragezone.com/f365/tut-508-99-shopping-548372/"]http://forum.ragezone.com/f365/tut-508-99-shopping-548372/[/URL]
Heres the code version and I'll post a pic also.
[CODE] .\Bulby\content\ShopHandler.java:268: cannot find symbol symbol : method setAccessMask(Bulby.players.Player,int,int,int,int,int) location: class Bulby.io.Frames p.frames.setAccessMask(p, 1278, 23, 620, 0, 40); ^ .\Bulby\content\ShopHandler.java:278: cannot find symbol symbol : method setAccessMask(Bulby.players.Player,int,int,int,int,int) location: class Bulby.io.Frames p.frames.setAccessMask(p, 1278, 24, 620, 0, 40); ^ .\Bulby\content\ShopHandler.java:407: cannot find symbol symbol : method runScript(Bulby.players.Player,int,java.lang.Object[],java.lang .String) location: class Bulby.io.Frames p.frames.runScript(p, 25, setshopparams, "vg");//Loads main stock items ^ .\Bulby\content\ShopHandler.java:408: cannot find symbol symbol : method runScript(Bulby.players.Player,int,java.lang.Object[],java.lang .String) location: class Bulby.io.Frames p.frames.runScript(p, 150, invparams, "IviiiIsssssssss"); ^ .\Bulby\content\ShopHandler.java:409: cannot find symbol symbol : method runScript(Bulby.players.Player,int,java.lang.Object[],java.lang .String) location: class Bulby.io.Frames p.frames.runScript(p, 150, shopparams, "IviiiIsssssssss"); ^ .\Bulby\content\ShopHandler.java:410: cannot find symbol symbol : method setAccessMask(Bulby.players.Player,int,int,int,int,int) location: class Bulby.io.Frames p.frames.setAccessMask(p, 1278, 0, 621, 0, 28); ^ .\Bulby\content\ShopHandler.java:419: cannot find symbol symbol : method setAccessMask(Bulby.players.Player,int,int,int,int,int) location: class Bulby.io.Frames p.frames.setAccessMask(p, 1278, 23, 620, 0, 40); ^ .\Bulby\content\ShopHandler.java:427: cannot find symbol symbol : method setAccessMask(Bulby.players.Player,int,int,int,int,int) location: class Bulby.io.Frames p.frames.setAccessMask(p, 1278, 24, 620, 0, 40); ^ 8 errors Press any key to continue . . . item.title: [HELP] Problem with cannot find symbol
item.description:
@11167 wrote:

In the file Frames, you must define the methods:
setAccessMask and runScript. Something like:
public void setAccessMask(Player p, int a, int b, int c, int d, int e) { }
public void runScript(Player p, int a, Object[] b, String c) { }

Of course, I don’t know what p, a, b, c, d, or e do. You gotta figure those out on your own (hint: I just looked at what couldn’t be found)
